Germany

Regular Season Round 11: Herzogenaurach - Ansbach 93-105

Date: November 30, 2019

Not a big story in a game when 11th ranked Herzogenaurach (4-6) lost at home to first ranked Ansbach (9-2) 105-93 on Saturday. Ansbach outrebounded Herzogenaurach 45-34 including 30 on the defensive glass. They looked well-organized offensively handing out 21 assists. American point guard TyLik Evans (173-96, college: USC Aiken) orchestrated the victory by scoring 30 points, 7 rebounds, 6 assists and 4 steals. Forward Simon Walter (202-89, college: Cumberland) contributed with 23 points and 7 rebounds for the winners. Austrian swingman Michael Kaiser (195-82) answered with 25 points, 6 rebounds and 6 assists and Matthias Schlindwein added 18 points and 9 rebounds in the effort for Herzogenaurach. Both teams had four players each who scored in double figures. Ansbach have an impressive series of six victories in a row. They maintain first place in South-East with 9-2 record. Loser Herzogenaurach dropped to the twelfth position with six games lost. Ansbach will face Muenchen OSB (#14) at home in the next round which should be an easy win for them. Herzogenaurach will play against FC Bayern III in Muenchen and hope to win that game.
